snippet.title: 5 Must Watch Things You MISSED in January 2026 and 5 You WON'T Want To Miss in February 2026
snippet.description:
Don't miss out on the entertainment everyone's talking about! Join us as we explore January's hidden gems you might have overlooked and February's upcoming releases that deserve your attention. From Sam Raimi's return to horror with "Send Help" to Emerald Fennell's unique take on "Wuthering Heights," we've got your watchlist covered! Our roundup includes the Mel Brooks documentary, "Scrubs" revival, Idris Elba in "Hijack," Gore Verbinski's time-travel thriller, spy comedy "Ponies," The Muppets' variety show return, the experimental horror of "28 Years Later: The Bone Temple," and the legacy-focused "Scream 7." What are you looking forward to watching next? Let us know in the comments!
